<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1972-12-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1969-01-11T15:50:00-05:00" n="224" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d224">
                        <head>224. Editorial Note</head>
                        <p>During a fifteen-minute meeting on September 24, 1972, President
                                <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Henry Kissinger</persName> discussed the situation
                            in Uganda and also devoted some attention to Burundi. For a transcript
                            of the conversation, see <ref target="#d258">Document 258</ref>.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>